<body>
    <h1>DevQL Capability Architecture: Core vs First-Party Plugins and Futu=
re Third-Party Model</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFu=
tureThird-PartyModel-DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsan=
dFutureThird-PartyModel">DevQL Capability Architecture: Core vs First-Party=
 Plugins and Future Third-Party Model</h1>
<p><em>Date: March 16, 2026</em></p>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-Purpose">Purpose</h2>
<p>This page documents:</p>
<p>a) the reasoning behind the plugin approach <br>
b) the classification of planned capabilities into Core vs first-party plug=
ins <br>
c) how first-party plugins will be implemented <br>
d) how third-party plugins can work in the future, and what we must impleme=
nt now to support that safely.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-A)WhyaPluginApproach">A) Why a Plugin Approach</h2>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-1)Problemwearesolving">1) Problem we are solving</h2>
<p>We are adding multiple advanced capabilities (Blast Radius, Knowledge, S=
emantic Clones, Test Harness) that evolve at different speeds, have differe=
nt dependencies, and may require different storage/computation profiles.</p=
>
<p>If everything is hardcoded into one DevQL monolith:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>every new capability forces central parser/executor changes</p></li>
<li>
<p>release risk increases as surface area grows</p></li>
<li>
<p>experimentation (models, heuristics, scoring) becomes harder</p></li>
<li>
<p>ownership boundaries are unclear</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-2)Whyapluginarchitectureistherightdirection">2) Why a plugin a=
rchitecture is the right direction</h2>
<p>A plugin-oriented capability model gives:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Separation of concerns</strong>: capability-specific logic stays=
 isolated</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Extensibility</strong>: new stages/ingesters can be added withou=
t destabilizing the core</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Safer evolution</strong>: we can iterate scoring/classification =
logic independently</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Operational flexibility</strong>: some capabilities can be enabl=
ed/disabled by deployment profile</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Future ecosystem readiness</strong>: clear host/plugin boundarie=
s enable third-party support later</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-3)Whynotmakeeverythingaplugin">3) Why not make everything a pl=
ugin</h2>
<p>Some concerns are foundational and cross-cutting. If they are pluginized=
 too early, we lose consistency and increase coordination cost.</p>
<p>Therefore, we keep a <strong>small, stable Core</strong> and move capabi=
lity-specific intelligence into plugins.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-B)CapabilityClassification:CorevsFirst-PartyPlugins">B) Capabi=
lity Classification: Core vs First-Party Plugins</h2>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-1)Plannedcapabilities(currentscope)">1) Planned capabilities (=
current scope)</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Capability</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Classification</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Rationale</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Blast Radius</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Core</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Foundational static graph substrate; other capabilities depend on artefa=
ct/dependency correctness.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Knowledge</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>First-party plugin</strong> on top of core provenance primitives=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ingestion/retrieval behavior varies by source and policy; should be modu=
lar. Core provides shared identity/version/relation primitives.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Semantic Clones</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>First-party plugin</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Model/provider/scoring choices evolve frequently; plugin boundary reduce=
s core churn.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Test Harness</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>First-party plugin</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Test linkage/classification/coverage heuristics are capability-specific =
and iterative.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-2)Coreplatformresponsibilities(notoptional)">2) Core platform =
responsibilities (not optional)</h2>
<p>Core must own:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>snapshot and temporal semantics (<code>repo</code>, <code>asOf</code>, c=
ommit-addressable truth)</p></li>
<li>
<p>canonical artefact/symbol model and dependency graph</p></li>
<li>
<p>query pipeline kernel (parse/validate/plan/execute)</p></li>
<li>
<p>stage registry and schema metadata registry</p></li>
<li>
<p>storage gateways and migration orchestration</p></li>
<li>
<p>provenance stamping and result traceability</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-C)First-PartyPluginImplementationModel">C) First-Party Plugin =
Implementation Model</h2>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-1)Runtimeshape">1) Runtime shape</h2>
<p>First-party plugins are implemented in-repo and loaded by a host registr=
y at startup.</p>
<p>Each plugin contributes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>query stages (e.g., <code>tests()</code>, <code>coverage()</code>, <code=
>semanticClones()</code>, <code>knowledge()</code>)</p></li>
<li>
<p>ingestion hooks (e.g., enrich-on-ingest, coverage ingest, connector inge=
st)</p></li>
<li>
<p>schema metadata for Query Explorer autocomplete</p></li>
<li>
<p>capability-specific migrations through host-controlled migration APIs</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-2)Suggestedplugincontract">2) Suggested plugin contract</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">trait C=
apabilityPlugin {
    fn id(&amp;self) -&gt; &amp;'static str;
    fn register_stages(&amp;self, stages: &amp;mut StageRegistry);
    fn register_ingesters(&amp;self, ingesters: &amp;mut IngestRegistry);
    fn register_schema(&amp;self, schema: &amp;mut QuerySchemaRegistry);
    fn migrate(&amp;self, migrator: &amp;mut Migrator) -&gt; anyhow::Result=
&lt;()&gt;;
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-3)Executionflow">3) Execution flow</h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>DevQL host boots</p></li>
<li>
<p>Host loads first-party plugin registry</p></li>
<li>
<p>Plugins register stages/ingesters/schema entries</p></li>
<li>
<p>Query parser resolves stage names through registry</p></li>
<li>
<p>Executor invokes stage handlers through typed host context</p></li>
<li>
<p>Outputs are schema-validated, provenance-stamped, and returned</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-4)Implementationconstraintsforfirst-partyplugins">4) Implement=
ation constraints for first-party plugins</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>plugin code does not bypass host abstractions</p></li>
<li>
<p>storage access should go through host gateways (not raw unrestricted SQL=
 everywhere)</p></li>
<li>
<p>every plugin stage has typed args and typed outputs</p></li>
<li>
<p>plugin-produced data includes <code>capability_id</code> and version met=
adata for traceability</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-D)FutureThird-PartyPluginModelandWhatWeNeedNow">D) Future Thir=
d-Party Plugin Model and What We Need Now</h2>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-1)Futurethird-partymodel">1) Future third-party model</h2>
<p>We should support third-party plugins as <strong>out-of-process</strong>=
 components (separate binary/WASM), not arbitrary in-process code.</p>
<p>High-level model:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>plugin package contains manifest + executable/WASM + signature</p></li>
<li>
<p>host validates compatibility and trust policy</p></li>
<li>
<p>plugin performs handshake with host (capabilities, stages, required perm=
issions)</p></li>
<li>
<p>stage/ingest calls happen over stable RPC (e.g., JSON-RPC/gRPC)</p></li>
<li>
<p>host enforces timeouts, resource limits, scope checks, output validation=
</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-2)Permissionscopesforthird-partyplugins">2) Permission scopes =
for third-party plugins</h2>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>read_source</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>read_git_metadata</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>read_events</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>write_plugin_namespace</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>network</code> (explicitly opt-in)</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Default policy should be least-privilege and deny-by-default.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-3)Whatwemustimplementnow(requiredfoundation)">3) What we must =
implement now (required foundation)</h2>
<p>To avoid a costly retrofit later, we should implement these now even for=
 first-party plugins:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Capability metadata model</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>id, version, api_version, declared required scopes</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Host-controlled execution context</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>stage handlers receive a constrained host context, not ambient unrestric=
ted access</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Storage gateway abstraction</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>namespaced writes and typed storage APIs</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Stage I/O schema contracts</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>typed argument and output validation at registry boundary</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Provenance stamping</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>persist capability id/version/run metadata with outputs</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Versioned plugin API</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>explicit compatibility handshake for future third-party adapters</p></li=
>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Policy hooks</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>enable/disable by capability; future scope-approval checks</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-4)Practicalsequencing">4) Practical sequencing</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Phase 1</strong>: Registry-based first-party plugin architecture=
 in-process</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Phase 2</strong>: Permission-aware host context and storage gate=
ways</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Phase 3</strong>: External plugin runtime adapter (RPC)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Phase 4</strong>: Packaging/signing/trust-policy UX</p></li>
</ul>
<p>This keeps near-term delivery fast while ensuring long-term extensibilit=
y and safety.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DevQLCapabilityArchitecture:CorevsFirst-PartyPluginsandFutureThir=
d-PartyModel-Summary">Summary</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Keep Core minimal, stable, and foundational.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Treat Blast Radius as Core.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Implement Knowledge, Semantic Clones, and Test Harness as first-party pl=
ugins.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Introduce execution/storage/schema/provenance boundaries now so third-pa=
rty plugins become an extension, not a redesign.</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
